Such a lonely life.  Millions of people love them and they have one another plus their families and a few friends.   But their lives are extremely hectic with relatively little down time.  I feel incredibly bad for them.  They can't live normally.  They're always surrounded by staff to protect them from those crazy fans who have no boundaries.  They can't easily just walk out the door and go to the mall or out to eat without major hassle or the risk of being seen and possibly accosted by some because they're so well known.  Yes, they chose the idol life.  But I doubt at their tender ages they really understood the ramifications of stardom, especially when they've become a household name with a massive Army.  They are human beings first and foremost and we need to remember that.

He gave up looking and went to the person who he's supposedly to meet up with and rang the bell that's when he disappeared. 2nd: Jimin was just chilling and scrolling through his phone, as he came across something shocking on his phone, his eyes widened and then he  disappeared through his phone. 3rd: If you look into the room Rm was in, the picture next to the mirror was blank with nothing written on it. He also about to go back to scrolling through his phone  but then he disappeared. After his disappearance, where the couch was it said " Super Casting" 5th: J-Hope was in the dance studio ( keep in mind that it's not same one where rm was in) practicing his dance skills or he was just trying to have a fun way of exercising through dancing, anyways when he was done he went closer to the mirror pushed it with all of his courage  because he most likely made eye contact with the same thing rm saw in those mirrors and disappeared.
